idence and policy analysis in Colombia -- tConclusion: Building capacity for policy analysis amid tensions and challenges in Colombia -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aLeading Colombian academics and experienced policy practitioners cast new light on their country in this systematic overview of policy analysis for an international audience. Examining the historical development and current status of policy analysis as a field of study and in practice, it considers public policy analysis in government and the judiciary, and across domains including health, education and the military. Contributors also delve into Colombia’s notable success in economic regeneration, the management of cultural diversity and the resolution of long-term internal armed conflict. Not just an important summation of policy analysis in Colombia, this book also provides insights and lessons applicable elsewhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aAppe, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvellaneda, Claudia N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBello-Gómez, Ricardo A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBitar, Sebastián, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaballero-Argáez, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuzmán-Botero, Andrés, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGélvez-Ferreira, Juan David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsaza, Carolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voca